     <div type="encomium">
   <head>Metaphrasti Dignissimo.</head>
   <l>TO Translate <hi>Seneca,</hi> and to obserue</l>
   <l>His Brevity, and from his sence not swerue,</l>
   <l>Require's a Learned Iudgement ev'n in Prose;</l>
   <l>But him in Verse to render, and yet lose</l>
   <l>Neither his Quicknes, nor his Eloquence,</l>
   <l>Shew's both great Skill and our Tongu's Excellence;</l>
   <l>Thus by this happy Version may we see,</l>
   <l>That the Acutest Prose is <hi>Poetry,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And may beleeve that <hi>Seneca'</hi> as in name</l>
   <l>Both <hi>Poet</hi> and <hi>Philosopher's</hi> the same.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. C.</signed>
   </closer>
